Call Forth the Dweller				TYPE:Incantation	SCHOOL:Divination			CLASSES:ALL=6[PREVARGTEQ:UA_VAR_USEINCANTATION,1]	COMPS:V, S, M, F, XP	CASTTIME:60 Minutes	RANGE:Personal	TARGETAREA:You.	DURATION:Instantanous	SAVEINFO:None	SPELLRES:No	DESC:This incantation contacts the enigmatic, extradimensional being known as the Dweller on the Threshold, an entity that imparts knowledge about its specifi c obsession: doors and other entrances. Failure: If the caster fails two consecutive Knowledge (arcana) checks, the Dweller on the Threshold gleefully lies, employing falsehoods that demonstrate its inclination toward mischief and cruelty. Skill Check: Knowledge (arcana) DC 20, 6 successes. Failure: If the caster fails two consecutive Knowledge (arcana) checks, the Dweller on the Threshold gleefully lies, employing falsehoods that demonstrate its inclination toward mischief and cruelty. Material Component: Forty-two mystic symbols inscribed around the perimeter of the focus doorway (requiring materials costing 500 gp). As described above, these symbols gradually disappear during the time the incantation is in effect. Focus: An open doorway large enough to allow a Medium creature to pass through it. XP Component: 400 XP. Backlash: After speaking with the Dweller on the Threshold, the caster is exhausted.	SOURCEPAGE:UA		COST:500	XPCOST:400					
